Hardware Components:
Display: Displaytech INT035TFT-TS}
3.5" TFT LCD, 320×240 QVGA resolution.
8080-style parallel interface via SSD1963 controller.
4-wire resistive touchscreen via MAX11802 (SPI).

Main:
Arduino ASX00039 GIGA Display Shield 3.97" Touchscreen 800x480 Mic IMU

Features: 
Note: The GIGA Display Shield requires a GIGA R1 WiFi board to function. It has no microcontroller and cannot be
programmed independently.

1. KD040WVFID026-01-C025A 3.97" TFT Display
480x800 resolution
16.7 million colors
0.108 mm pixel size
Capacitive Touch sensor
5-point and gesture support
Edge LED backlight

2. BMI270 6-axis IMU (Accelerometer and Gyroscope)
16-bit
3-axis accelerometer with ±2g/±4g/±8g/±16g range
3-axis gyroscope with ±125dps/±250dps/±500dps/±1000dps/±2000dps range

3. SMLP34RGB2W3 RGB LED
Common Anode
IS31FL3197-QFLS2-TR Driver with integrated charge pump

4. MP34DT06JTR Digital Microphone
AOP = 122.5 dbSPL
64 dB signal-to-noise ratio
Omnidirectional sensitivity
–26 dBFS ± 3 dB sensitivity

5. I/O
GIGA Connector
2.54 mm Camera Connecto


Microcontroller: Arduino Mega 2560
16-bit data bus support.
Flash and SRAM for graphics and game logic.

Wiring Summary:
16 data pins + 5 control lines for TFT.
SPI lines for touch: MOSI, MISO, SCK, CS.
